# AlgoViz — Algorithm Visualizer

An interactive, dark-themed algorithm visualizer with step-by-step animations for all major sorting and searching algorithms.

## 🚀 Quick Start

```bash
python3 server.py
```

Then open [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080) in your browser.  
*(The browser opens automatically.)*

---

## 📦 Files

```
algorithm_visualizer/
├── index.html   — Main UI structure
├── style.css    — Dark futuristic theme
├── app.js       — All algorithm logic + canvas rendering
└── server.py    — Python HTTP server
```

---

## 🔢 Sorting Algorithms

| Algorithm      | Best       | Average    | Worst      | Space    | Stable |
|---------------|------------|------------|------------|----------|--------|
| Bubble Sort    | O(n)       | O(n²)      | O(n²)      | O(1)     | Yes    |
| Selection Sort | O(n²)      | O(n²)      | O(n²)      | O(1)     | No     |
| Insertion Sort | O(n)       | O(n²)      | O(n²)      | O(1)     | Yes    |
| Merge Sort     | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(n)     | Yes    |

## 🔍 Searching Algorithms

| Algorithm            | Best   | Average     | Worst    | Requires Sorted |
|---------------------|--------|-------------|----------|----------------|
| Linear Search        | O(1)   | O(n)        | O(n)     | No             |
| Binary Search        | O(1)   | O(log n)    | O(log n) | Yes            |

---

## 🎮 Controls

- **NEW ARRAY** — Regenerate a random array
- **▶ SORT / ▶ SEARCH** — Start the animation
- **■ STOP** — Halt the animation mid-run
- **Array Size** — Adjust number of elements (10–120)
- **Speed** — Control animation speed (1=slow, 10=fast)
- **Target (search)** — Leave blank for a random target

## 🎨 Color Legend

**Sorting:**
- 🟦 Default bar
- 🟡 Comparing
- 🔴 Swapping
- 🟢 Sorted
- 🟣 Pivot

**Searching:**
- 🟦 Default / Search range
- 🟡 Currently checking
- 🟢 Found
- ⬛ Discarded

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.6+
- Any modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari)
- No external dependencies needed
